wdi-IE.PPN.TRAN.CD.def: Public Private Partnerships in transport (current US$)  is the value of commitments to transportation projects that have reached financial closure and directly or indirectly serve the public, including lease and management contracts, operation and management contracts with major capital expenditure, and greenfield projects (in which a private entity or public-private joint venture builds and operates a new facility). It excludes divestitures and merchant projects. Movable assets and small projects are excluded.
wdi-IE.PPN.TRAN.CD.name: Public private partnerships investment in transport
wdi-IE.PPN.TRAN.CD.source: World Bank, Private Participation in Infrastructure Project Database (http://ppi.worldbank.org).
wdi-IE.PPN.TRAN.CD.dataset: World Bank, Private Participation in Infrastructure Project Database (http://ppi.worldbank.org).
